LEGIONELLOSIS - USA (21): (NORTH CAROLINA) FATAL, AGRICULTURAL FAIR
*******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 27 Sep 2019
Source: ABC News 4 [edited]
https://abcnews4.com/news/local/update-legionnaires-cases-in-buncombe-increase-from-15-to-20


On Friday [27 Sep 2019], Buncombe County Health and Human Services (BCHHS) reports 20 confirmed cases of Legionnaires' disease in the county, including one fatality, as of 5 p.m. on Thursday [26 Sep 2019]. This is an increase of 5 confirmed cases since the last Buncombe County report on Thu 26 Sep 2019. Henderson County now reports 22 confirmed cases, up from 12 on Thursday. The state is now reporting over 60 cases in North and South Carolina, up from 25 confirmed cases on Thursday.

Here is the NC breakdown of confirmed cases by county for Fri 27 Sep 2019 from the NC Department of Health and Human Services: Buncombe - 21 (20 cases, 1 fatality);
Haywood - 5; Henderson - 22; Madison - 1; McDowell - 2; Mecklenburg - 2; Mitchell - 1; Rutherford - 1; Transylvania - 2; Yancey - 1; and Out of state (SC) - 5.

To check the status of the WNC outbreak of Legionnaires' disease, click here: https://epi.dph.ncdhhs.gov/cd/legionellosis/outbreak.html [See item 2 below. - Mod.ML].

BCHHS says it is continuing to work with local providers to identify and investigate additional cases. It has no new information other than case counts to report at this time.

Buncombe County residents with questions about Legionnaires' disease can call Buncombe County Communicable Disease at 828-250-5109.

